<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN282-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai + tuṟai lost. pālaipāṭiya peruṅkaṭuṅkō.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN282">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>eḵkuḷaṅ kaḻiya virunila maruṅki</l>
<l>ṉaruṅkaṭa ṉiṟutta peruñce yāḷaṉai</l>
<l>yāṇṭuḷa ṉōveṉa viṉavuti yāyiṉ</l>
<l>varupaṭait tāṅkiya kiḷartā rakala</l>
<l>maruṅkaṭa ṉiṟumār vayava reṟiya</l>
<l>vuṭampun tōṉṟā vuyirkkeṭ ṭaṉṟē</l>
<l>malaiyunar maṭaṅki māṟetirk kaḻiya</l>
<l>valakaip pōki citaintuvē ṟākiya</l>
<l>palakai yallatu kaḷattoḻi yātē</l>
<l>cēṇviḷaṅku nallicai niṟīi</l>
<l>nānaviṟ pulavar vāyu ḷāṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>If you were to ask ask</l>
<l>about the lord doing great [things] who performed a difficult duty</l>
<l>on the dark ground, when a lance pierced [his] inside </l>
<l>	“where is he?”,</l>
<l>when strong men in order to perform [their] difficult duty attacked</l>
<l>[his] bright-garlanded chest that endured the coming weapons,</l>
<l>his breath was lost, without [his] body appearing, [however].</l>
<l>When the enemies after surrendering passed out in the face of opposition,</l>
<l>nothing but the shield stayed behind on the [battle] field</l>
<l>that had become different, wasted, the demonesses having gone.</l>
<l>He exists [still] in the mouth of poets excercising [their] tongues,</l>
<l>establishing [his] fame that shines in the distance.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
